1
00:00:00,209 --> 00:00:03,334
On the fourth day I got someone to bring me a cigarette

2
00:00:05,417 --> 00:00:07,959
Interviewer: How?
Witness: With money

3
00:00:10,959 --> 00:00:16,584
With money, when you go in they take everything from you

4
00:00:17,792 --> 00:00:19,667
You go in without anything on you

5
00:00:19,834 --> 00:00:24,250
No money or anything else, they take it all

6
00:00:24,417 --> 00:00:27,792
Imagine, when I got out my money was missing

7
00:00:29,417 --> 00:00:31,500
I knew exactly how much I had handed in

8
00:00:32,209 --> 00:00:36,083
Eighteen thousand was missing, they took it

9
00:00:38,292 --> 00:00:40,292
Interviewer: Who took it?
Witness: Them, who else

10
00:00:40,417 --> 00:00:42,375
They were the ones I gave the belongings to

11
00:00:42,626 --> 00:00:44,292
They were supposed to be safe-keeping

12
00:00:50,292 --> 00:00:53,375
Interviewer: Who brought you the cigarette?
Witness: Just someone

13
00:00:53,959 --> 00:00:58,125
I swear to you it was one of them, I swear he was ISIS

14
00:01:00,083 --> 00:01:02,417
I bought it from him and told him, When I get out

15
00:01:03,334 --> 00:01:04,876
Come to me so I can pay you

16
00:01:06,500 --> 00:01:08,209
The cigarette cost 25,000

17
00:01:11,167 --> 00:01:14,876
And a whole pack outside cost 18,000

18
00:01:16,209 --> 00:01:18,542
A pack was 18,000

19
00:01:18,542 --> 00:01:20,500
And I bought the cigarette from him for 25,000

20
00:01:21,626 --> 00:01:23,542
Interviewer: How did you smoke it and what happened?

21
00:01:23,542 --> 00:01:27,000
How did I smoke it, of course he brought it hidden

22
00:01:27,375 --> 00:01:29,834
He put it inside a <i>samoon</i> [bread roll]

23
00:01:31,375 --> 00:01:34,918
When I took the loaf I put it in my hand and hid it

24
00:01:36,792 --> 00:01:41,334
I wrapped it in clothes and inside my pants

25
00:01:42,417 --> 00:01:44,918
We didn’t wear belts because they took them away

26
00:01:45,500 --> 00:01:49,042
It was cold, and in the bathroom

27
00:01:49,334 --> 00:01:52,292
There was an electric heater hanging on the wall

28
00:01:53,709 --> 00:01:57,500
When the door closed, I smoked a little of it

29
00:01:57,667 --> 00:01:58,876
Then I put it out

30
00:01:59,667 --> 00:02:04,709
Then I wrapped it in my clothes and went back inside

31
00:02:05,125 --> 00:02:09,709
I smoked it over two days, secretly

32
00:02:10,292 --> 00:02:13,876
If they had seen me that would have been the end

33
00:02:14,292 --> 00:02:16,751
My punishment was 20 lashes and it would have become 60

34
00:02:17,500 --> 00:02:19,042
I was imprisoned for smoking

35
00:02:19,083 --> 00:02:20,792
So imagine me smoking inside

36
00:02:21,167 --> 00:02:22,959
They would have punished me much harder

37
00:02:24,918 --> 00:02:26,709
Interviewer: Did anyone know you were smoking?

38
00:02:26,751 --> 00:02:28,125
One person knew about it

39
00:02:29,542 --> 00:02:32,876
He was a prisoner who found out about me

40
00:02:33,959 --> 00:02:36,626
On the third time, half the cigarette was left

41
00:02:37,167 --> 00:02:40,792
I wanted to smoke it, but suddenly someone noticed and knocked on the door

42
00:02:42,417 --> 00:02:45,876
He said to me, God protect you, if you have one, give me just two puffs

43
00:02:46,292 --> 00:02:47,834
Don’t worry, I swear I won’t tell anyone

44
00:02:48,667 --> 00:02:51,709
I told him come in, I gave him two puffs then I put it out

45
00:02:52,459 --> 00:02:56,792
A little was left, I smoked it three hours later

46
00:02:57,751 --> 00:03:02,250
And the one who sold me the cigarette was one of their members

47
00:03:04,709 --> 00:03:06,918
Interviewer: Did you know him before?
Witness: No, I didn’t

48
00:03:08,334 --> 00:03:10,959
Interviewer: How did you manage to talk to him

49
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:12,626
And ask him to bring you a cigarette?

50
00:03:12,667 --> 00:03:17,709
When they bring tea, they open the prison door

51
00:03:19,167 --> 00:03:21,542
And there is a room across from the prison

52
00:03:22,292 --> 00:03:26,959
They threw the cigarettes inside it

53
00:03:28,417 --> 00:03:31,918
When they go down, they take two prisoners out

54
00:03:31,918 --> 00:03:33,792
They took the same ones every day

55
00:03:33,834 --> 00:03:35,334
When they confiscated cigarettes

56
00:03:35,834 --> 00:03:39,417
Quantities could be five, six, or 10 cartons

57
00:03:40,250 --> 00:03:42,876
They took those two, made them carry them upstairs

58
00:03:42,918 --> 00:03:46,876
They carried them up

59
00:03:48,042 --> 00:03:49,834
We told them, Steal something for us

60
00:03:49,876 --> 00:03:51,959
We didn’t know them, I personally didn’t

61
00:03:52,709 --> 00:03:54,083
I wanted to see who they were the first time

62
00:03:54,125 --> 00:03:57,292
So I told them, Steal a pack and hide it

63
00:03:57,500 --> 00:03:59,959
And bring it for us to smoke, but he refused

64
00:04:01,042 --> 00:04:03,584
And when he brought in the tea I asked him, What are these cigarettes

65
00:04:04,292 --> 00:04:05,876
He said, Don’t you know cigarettes are banned

66
00:04:06,000 --> 00:04:07,709
I said, Yes I know they are banned

67
00:04:08,042 --> 00:04:09,959
I told him, I haven’t smoked for four days

68
00:04:10,751 --> 00:04:14,876
I swear I’m going to lose it and explode

69
00:04:15,834 --> 00:04:20,709
He told me, Dry the tea leaves with heat

70
00:04:20,959 --> 00:04:22,542
And roll them in paper and smoke them

71
00:04:22,751 --> 00:04:24,292
I told him, That’s not enough

72
00:04:26,083 --> 00:04:31,042
And when he brought tea at sunset and opened the door

73
00:04:32,250 --> 00:04:35,292
The boy went to get the tea so I got up with him

74
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:40,876
I told him, Haj, your mouth smells of cigarettes

75
00:04:40,918 --> 00:04:42,125
Don’t tell me that’s not true

76
00:04:42,167 --> 00:04:43,459
He told me, I used to smoke before

77
00:04:43,959 --> 00:04:45,876
And I realized he smoked too

78
00:04:47,626 --> 00:04:52,375
I swear to you, the café where we used to sit

79
00:04:52,876 --> 00:04:54,959
Didn’t we smoke hiding in the corner

80
00:04:55,500 --> 00:05:00,834
I swear to you two of them wore jackets with Hisba written on them

81
00:05:01,250 --> 00:05:03,959
They came in and opened the cigarette packs

82
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:05,667
Each one had his own brand

83
00:05:05,709 --> 00:05:09,042
I remember one smoked Gauloises and I don’t recall the other

84
00:05:09,918 --> 00:05:13,334
They smoked five, six, seven cigarettes

85
00:05:13,459 --> 00:05:16,834
They drank tea while sitting then left

86
00:05:17,834 --> 00:05:22,083
I swear to you, as I told you, they were smoking cigarettes
